gic figure who sought to save Rome from its enemies and the corrupting influence of Christianity. Christian writers and historians have seen Julian much differently: as a traitor to God and violent oppressor of Christians. Had Julian not been killed by a random Persian spear, he might well have changed all of history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aChristianity and other religionsxRoman2DLC. 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-6002DLC. 0aPaganismzRome2DLC. 0aReligion and statezRome2DLC. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Royalty.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z978311131826408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074978640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300274523?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300274523423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300274523/original  a978-3-11-074978-6  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131826-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023